Identifier

Source: R/Id.R
new_id.Rd

Generate a new unique identifier.

new_id()

Value

Id object.

Details

Identifiers are made using the UUIDgenerate.

See also

UUIDgenerate.

Examples

# create new id
i <- new_id()

# print id
print(i)
#> Found more than one class "Id" in cache; using the first, from namespace 'prioritizr'
#> Also defined by 'DBI'
#> Found more than one class "Id" in cache; using the first, from namespace 'prioritizr'
#> Also defined by 'DBI'
#> Found more than one class "Id" in cache; using the first, from namespace 'prioritizr'
#> Also defined by 'DBI'
#> id: 9045c069-cb69-4fba-86a3-e195ec0fc6ef

# convert to character
as.character(i)
#> [1] "9045c069-cb69-4fba-86a3-e195ec0fc6ef"

# check if it is an Id object
is.Id(i)
#> [1] TRUE
